==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Alalia
<hw>A*la"li*a</hw> <pr>()</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
priv. + <?/ a talking; cf. <?/ speechless.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Inability to utter articulate sounds, due either to paralysis of
the larynx or to that form of aphasia, called <xex>motor</xex>, or
<xex>ataxis</xex>, <xex>aphasia</xex>, due to loss of control of the
muscles of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

